In this article, President Obama condemns the bombings in Jakarta, Indonesia and expresses his condolences to the victims and their families. He reassures the Indonesian people that the US government is ready to help and support them in responding to and recovering from the attacks. Obama acknowledges Indonesia's efforts in combating violent extremism but emphasizes that these attacks show that extremists are still committed to killing innocent people of any faith. He promises to continue partnering with Indonesia to eliminate the threat from these violent extremists and support a future of security and opportunity for the Indonesian people.